				=09
					<div id=3D"mw-content-text" class=3D"mw-body-content"><div class=3D"mw=
-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr"><div class=3D"shortd=
escription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style=3D"display:none">Mod=
ern form of the metric system</div>
<div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">"SI" redirec=
ts here. For the chemical element with symbol Si, see <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Silicon" title=3D"Silicon">Silicon</a>. For other uses,=
 see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SI_(disambiguation)" class=3D=
"mw-redirect mw-disambig" title=3D"SI (disambiguation)">SI (disambiguation)=
</a>.</div>
<p>

The <b>International System of Units</b>, internationally known by the abbr=
eviation <b>SI</b> (from French <span title=3D"French-language text"><i lan=
g=3D"fr">Syst=C3=A8me international d'unit=C3=A9s</i></span>), is the moder=
n form of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metric_system" title=
=3D"Metric system">metric system</a> and the world's most widely used <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/System_of_units_of_measurement" title=
=3D"System of units of measurement">system of measurement</a>. It is the on=
ly system of measurement with official status in nearly every country in th=
e world, employed in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Science" titl=
e=3D"Science">science</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Technol=
ogy" title=3D"Technology">technology</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Industry_(economics)" title=3D"Industry (economics)">industry</a>, =
and everyday <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Commerce" title=3D"Co=
mmerce">commerce</a>. The SI system is coordinated by the <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Bureau_of_Weights_and_Measures" title=
=3D"International Bureau of Weights and Measures">International Bureau of W=
eights and Measures</a>, which is abbreviated BIPM from <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/French_language" title=3D"French language">French</a>=
: <i lang=3D"fr">Bureau international des poids et mesures</i>.
</p>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
