p"><span title=3D"Page: 128">:=E2=80=8A128=E2=80=8A</span></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"SI_base_units">SI base unit=
s</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DInternatio=
nal_System_of_Units&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit sectio=
n: SI base units"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracke=
t">]</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SI_base_unit" title=
=3D"SI base unit">SI base unit</a></div>
<p>The SI selects seven units to serve as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/SI_base_unit" title=3D"SI base unit">base units</a>, corresponding =
to seven base physical quantities. They are the <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Second" title=3D"Second">second</a>, with the symbol <span cl=
ass=3D"nowrap">s</span>, which is the SI unit of the physical quantity of <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time" title=3D"Time">time</a>; the =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metre" title=3D"Metre">metre</a>, =
symbol <span class=3D"nowrap">m</span>, the SI unit of <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Length" title=3D"Length">length</a>; <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kilogram" title=3D"Kilogram">kilogram</a> (<span cl=
ass=3D"nowrap">kg</span>, the unit of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Mass" title=3D"Mass">mass</a>); <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Ampere" title=3D"Ampere">ampere</a> (<span class=3D"nowrap">A</span>, <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electric_current" title=3D"Electric c=
urrent">electric current</a>); <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kel=
vin" title=3D"Kelvin">kelvin</a> (<span class=3D"nowrap">K</span>, <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thermodynamic_temperature" title=3D"Therm=
odynamic temperature">thermodynamic temperature</a>); <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mole_(unit)" title=3D"Mole (unit)">mole</a> (<span clas=
s=3D"nowrap">mol</span>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amount_of=
_substance" title=3D"Amount of substance">amount of substance</a>); and <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Candela" title=3D"Candela">candela</a=
> (<span class=3D"nowrap">cd</span>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Luminous_intensity" title=3D"Luminous intensity">luminous intensity</a>)=
.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-SIBrochure9thEd_1-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_System_of_Units#cite_note-SIBroch=
ure9thEd-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">]</span></a></sup>
The base units are defined in terms of the defining constants.  For example=
, the kilogram is defined by taking the Planck constant <span class=3D"texh=
tml"><i>h</i></span> to be <span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"=
6966662607015000000=E2=99=A0"></span>6.626<span style=3D"margin-left:.25em;=
">070</span><span style=3D"margin-left:.25em;">15</span><span style=3D"marg=
in-left:0.25em;margin-right:0.15em;">=C3=97</span>10<sup>=E2=88=9234</sup>&=
nbsp;J=E2=8B=85s</span>, giving the expression in terms of the defining con=
stants<sup id=3D"cite_ref-SIBrochure9thEd_1-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_System_of_Units#cite_note-S=
IBrochure9thEd-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup class=3D"reference nowrap"><span title=3D"=
Page: 131">:=E2=80=8A131=E2=80=8A</span></sup>
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"nowrap"><span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=
=3D"7000100000000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>1&nbsp;kg</span> =3D <span class=
=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num">(<span class=
=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"7008299792458000000=E2=99=A0"></span>2=
99<span style=3D"margin-left:.25em;">792</span><span style=3D"margin-left:.=
25em;">458</span></span>)<sup>2</sup></span><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span=
><span class=3D"den">(<span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"69666=
62607015000000=E2=99=A0"></span>6.626<span style=3D"margin-left:.25em;">070=
</span><span style=3D"margin-left:.25em;">15</span><span style=3D"margin-le=
ft:0.25em;margin-right:0.15em;">=C3=97</span>10<sup>=E2=88=9234</sup></span=
>)(<span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"7009919263177000000=E2=
=99=A0"></span>9<span style=3D"margin-left:.25em;">192</span><span style=3D=
"margin-left:.25em;">631</span><span style=3D"margin-left:.25em;">770</span=
></span>)</span></span>=E2=81=A0</span><link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-=
style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=
=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num"><span class=3D"texhtml"><=
i>h</i></span><span style=3D"white-space: nowrap;">=E2=80=89</span><span cl=
ass=3D"texhtml">=CE=94<i>=CE=BD</i><sub>Cs</sub></span></span><span class=
=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den"><span class=3D"texhtml"><i>c</i></=
span><sup>2</sup></span></span>=E2=81=A0</span>.</span></dd></dl>
<p>All units in the SI can be expressed in terms of the base units, and the=
 base units serve as a preferred set for expressing or analysing the relati=
onships between units. The choice of which and even how many quantities to =
use as base quantities is not fundamental or even unique =E2=80=93 it is a =
matter of convention.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-SIBrochure9thEd_1-5" class=3D"refe=
rence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_System_of_Uni=
ts#cite_note-SIBrochure9thEd-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup class=3D"reference nowrap">:=
=E2=80=8A<span title=3D"Page: 126
Quotation: &quot;... the choice of the base units was never unique, but gre=
w historically and became familiar to users of the SI&quot;" class=3D"toolt=
ip tooltip-dashed" style=3D"border-bottom: 1px dashed;">126</span>=E2=80=8A=
</sup>
</p>
