<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Metric_units_not_recognised=
_by_SI">Metric units not recognised by SI</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection=
"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DInternational_System_of_Units&amp;action=3Ded=
it&amp;section=3D23" title=3D"Edit section: Metric units not recognised by =
SI"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></s=
pan></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_metric_units=
" title=3D"List of metric units">List of metric units</a></div>
<p>Although the term <i>metric system</i> is often used as an informal alte=
rnative name for the International System of Units,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Metr=
icSystemAsNameForSI_59-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/International_System_of_Units#cite_note-MetricSystemAsNameForSI=
-59"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>47<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup> other metric systems exist, some of which were in widespre=
ad use in the past or are even still used in particular areas. There are al=
so individual <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metric_units" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Metric units">metric units</a> such as the <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sverdrup" title=3D"Sverdrup">sverdrup</a=
> and the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Darcy_(unit)" title=3D"D=
arcy (unit)">darcy</a> that exist outside of any system of units. Most of t=
he units of the other metric systems are not recognised by the SI.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Unacceptable_uses">Unaccept=
able uses</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-=
bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DIn=
ternational_System_of_Units&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D24" title=3D"Ed=
it section: Unacceptable uses"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-edits=
ection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Sometimes, SI unit name variations are introduced, mixing information ab=
out the corresponding physical quantity or the conditions of its measuremen=
t; however, this practice is unacceptable with the SI. "Unacceptability of =
mixing information with units: When one gives the value of a quantity, any =
information concerning the quantity or its conditions of measurement must b=
e presented in such a way as not to be associated with the unit."<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-SIBrochure_16-8" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/International_System_of_Units#cite_note-SIBrochure-16"><span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>10<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></=
sup>
Instances include: "<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Watt-peak" cla=
ss=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Watt-peak">watt-peak</a>" and "<a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Watt_RMS" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Watt RMS"=
>watt RMS</a>"; "<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geopotential_metr=
e" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Geopotential metre">geopotential metre</a=
>" and "<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vertical_metre" class=3D"m=
w-redirect" title=3D"Vertical metre">vertical metre</a>"; "<a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standard_cubic_metre" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Standard cubic metre">standard cubic metre</a>"; "<a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atomic_second" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Atomic se=
cond">atomic second</a>", "<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ephemer=
is_second" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Ephemeris second">ephemeris secon=
d</a>", and "<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sidereal_second" clas=
s=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Sidereal second">sidereal second</a>".
</p>
